WEBVTT

00:07.137 --> 00:10.140
[rock music]

00:10.184 --> 00:11.663
- No, Earl,
Mike's got it right.

00:11.707 --> 00:14.492
It's not about money.
It's about population control.

00:14.536 --> 00:16.494
- Yeah, I get that.
How far away are you?

00:16.538 --> 00:18.148
- I'm about 20 minutes away.

00:18.192 --> 00:19.193
- Well, let me know
when you get here.

00:19.236 --> 00:20.542
We got to talk about this.

00:20.585 --> 00:21.978
- I'll call you
when I'm almost there.

00:22.022 --> 00:23.632
- Okay, I'll see you
when you get here.

00:23.675 --> 00:25.547
- Bye.

00:25.590 --> 00:30.204
♪

00:30.247 --> 00:33.381
[grunts]

00:33.424 --> 00:34.512
[sighs]

00:40.910 --> 00:42.477
- Oh, no.

00:42.520 --> 00:44.522
- It's okay, man.
Just go.

00:44.566 --> 00:46.481
- I got two DUIs.
I can't get another.

00:46.524 --> 00:47.612
- Seriously, it's fine.

00:47.656 --> 00:48.744
Just get out of here.

00:48.787 --> 00:49.919
- That's not right.

00:49.962 --> 00:51.399
I might have a few bucks.

00:51.442 --> 00:53.575
- I don't want your money.

00:53.618 --> 00:54.967
[police car beeps]

00:58.275 --> 01:01.148
[tense music]

01:01.191 --> 01:02.758
There's no problem here.

01:02.801 --> 01:05.021
We were just working it out.

01:05.065 --> 01:06.936
- You the driver of this car?

01:06.979 --> 01:08.068
- Uh, yeah.

01:08.111 --> 01:10.070
- Can I see
your driver's license?

01:10.113 --> 01:11.114
- We were just talking.

01:11.158 --> 01:14.422
♪

01:14.465 --> 01:15.466
[clears throat]

01:17.033 --> 01:19.079
- I smell alcohol on you, sir.

01:19.122 --> 01:20.123
- No, please.

01:20.167 --> 01:21.603
- I'm not arresting you, sir,

01:21.646 --> 01:22.995
but I need you to have a seat
in the back of my car.

01:23.039 --> 01:24.127
Come on.

01:25.476 --> 01:27.174
- Come on, man.
- We're just gonna talk, okay?

01:27.217 --> 01:29.001
- Hey, you really didn't have
to do that, man.

01:29.045 --> 01:30.133
We were working it out.

01:30.177 --> 01:31.439
- We were working it out.

01:31.482 --> 01:32.875
- Listen, I'll handle
everything.

01:32.918 --> 01:34.485
Just take a moment,

01:34.529 --> 01:36.922
wait for me to come back, and
I'll be right with you, okay?

01:39.273 --> 01:40.796
- Cops, man.

01:40.839 --> 01:42.014
Good for hassling drunks,

01:42.058 --> 01:43.625
but never there
when we need you, right?

01:43.668 --> 01:45.496
- I'm here now, sir.

01:45.540 --> 01:48.020
I need your license
and registration.

01:48.064 --> 01:49.457
- Hey.

01:49.500 --> 01:51.981
Are you familiar with the term
"unreasonable searches"?

01:52.024 --> 01:53.287
Fourth amendment, pal.

01:53.330 --> 01:56.333
Do they even teach you that
at the academy?

01:56.377 --> 01:59.510
Hey, that's my personal
property, okay?

01:59.554 --> 02:01.512
- I said I need your license
and registration.

02:01.556 --> 02:03.906
[gunshot]
[grunts]

02:03.949 --> 02:07.083
[gunshots]

02:07.127 --> 02:13.872
♪

02:14.743 --> 02:16.484
- No, no, no, please!
I won't tell anybody!

02:16.527 --> 02:18.181
Please!
I'm sorry about your car!

02:18.225 --> 02:20.183
[gunshot]

02:20.227 --> 02:22.229
♪

02:27.625 --> 02:30.106
- Are you familiar with the
term "unreasonable searches?"

02:30.150 --> 02:31.629
Fourth amendment, pal.

02:31.673 --> 02:33.240
Do they even teach you that
at the academy?

02:33.283 --> 02:36.591
Hey, that's my personal
property, okay?

02:36.634 --> 02:38.288
- I said I need your license
and registration.

02:38.332 --> 02:41.857
[gunshots]

02:41.900 --> 02:44.033
- No, no, no, please!
I won't tell anybody!

02:44.076 --> 02:45.643
Please!
I'm sorry about your car!

02:45.687 --> 02:46.775
[gunshot]

02:46.818 --> 02:48.211
- Doug Timmons in action.

02:48.255 --> 02:51.214
Killed Officer Will Clement
of Loudonville PD,

02:51.258 --> 02:53.912
then killed Peter Bateman,
the guy who rear-ended him,

02:53.956 --> 02:56.001
and drove off in Bateman's car.

02:56.045 --> 02:57.394
- What was wrong with his?

02:57.438 --> 02:59.222
- The trunk wouldn't close
after the accident.

02:59.266 --> 03:00.963
- Threw the Loudonville cops
for a loop.

03:01.006 --> 03:02.051
Took them till this morning

03:02.094 --> 03:03.661
to get a BOLO out
on the right car.

03:03.705 --> 03:05.707
- Timmons used
armor-piercing ammo.

03:05.750 --> 03:07.752
It went straight through
the officer's vest.

03:07.796 --> 03:09.101
- He wasn't fooling around.

03:09.145 --> 03:11.365
He was looking for a showdown
with authority.

03:11.408 --> 03:14.498
- Play back the search
of the trunk.

03:14.542 --> 03:15.891
- Good for hassling drunks,

03:15.934 --> 03:17.240
but never there
when we need you, right?

03:17.284 --> 03:18.676
- I'm here now, sir.

03:18.720 --> 03:20.330
I need your license
and registration.

03:20.374 --> 03:22.245
- Hey, are you familiar
with the term

03:22.289 --> 03:23.551
"unreasonable searches"?

03:23.594 --> 03:25.074
Fourth amendment, pal.

03:25.117 --> 03:26.684
Do they even teach you that
at the academy?

03:26.728 --> 03:30.035
Hey, that's my personal
property, okay?

03:30.079 --> 03:31.689
- I said I need your license
and registration.

03:31.733 --> 03:34.083
- Freeze it.

03:34.126 --> 03:36.085
"Never there when we need you."

03:36.128 --> 03:37.913
Maybe law enforcement
let him down,

03:37.956 --> 03:40.089
or he thinks they did.

03:40.132 --> 03:41.917
Any record he's a crime victim?

03:41.960 --> 03:43.484
- I haven't found anything yet.

03:43.527 --> 03:45.181
No criminal record, either.

03:45.225 --> 03:48.315
He moved out of his last known
in Coblesmith eight months ago

03:48.358 --> 03:49.751
with no forwarding address.

03:49.794 --> 03:51.535
Social Security shows no work.

03:51.579 --> 03:54.321
He has no social media presence
at all.

03:54.364 --> 03:56.236
He's completely off the grid.

03:56.279 --> 03:58.586
- Hmm, that's not reassuring.
Any family?

03:58.629 --> 04:00.762
- No marriage, no kids,

04:00.805 --> 04:02.372
Dad died when Doug was 6,

04:02.416 --> 04:04.461
Mom had a stroke
when Doug was 17.

04:04.505 --> 04:06.289
She moved in with her sister
in Arizona.

04:06.333 --> 04:08.683
We have her place and phone
on surveillance.

04:08.726 --> 04:10.337
I haven't found any siblings
for Doug.

04:10.380 --> 04:13.949
[phone rings]

04:15.385 --> 04:18.432
- Something about the cop
looking in the trunk

04:18.475 --> 04:19.824
set him off.

04:19.868 --> 04:22.653
Hana, Kenny, and Clinton,
go over that car.

04:22.697 --> 04:24.960
Let's find out what Timmons
is worried about.

04:25.003 --> 04:27.963
- Loudonville cops said
they found nothing of interest.

04:28.006 --> 04:31.140
- We have different interests.

04:31.183 --> 04:33.098
- Tip just came in
off the wanted poster.

04:33.142 --> 04:36.406
An address for Timmons
in Loudonville.

04:36.450 --> 04:38.234
- I can't tell if he's scared
or hurt

04:38.278 --> 04:41.324
or just had
a bad night's sleep.

04:41.368 --> 04:44.806
I guess we'll ask him
when we find him.

04:44.849 --> 04:46.982
- I called soon as I saw
the poster,

04:47.025 --> 04:49.071
but you just missed him.

04:49.114 --> 04:50.464
So to speak.

04:50.507 --> 04:52.901
He cleared out
yesterday morning.

04:52.944 --> 04:54.468
Real nice kid.

04:54.511 --> 04:56.992
- How long has he been
staying here?

04:57.035 --> 04:58.167
- Three months.

04:58.210 --> 05:01.039
Always paid cash, on time.

05:01.083 --> 05:03.041
He wasn't around much.

05:03.085 --> 05:06.436
- Did he say why
he was moving out?

05:06.480 --> 05:08.612
- He seemed pretty down.

05:08.656 --> 05:11.920
He said he felt like
he was losing everything.

05:11.963 --> 05:14.966
So to speak.

05:15.010 --> 05:16.838
- Must have forgotten
about this.

05:16.881 --> 05:18.361
- Did he have a job somewhere?

05:18.405 --> 05:19.449
- I'm not sure.

05:19.493 --> 05:22.060
He said he wanted to get
a government job

05:22.104 --> 05:24.106
in Albany.

05:24.149 --> 05:25.673
- He wanted to work
for the government?

05:25.716 --> 05:27.196
- In Albany, yeah.

05:27.239 --> 05:28.850
He went there sometimes,

05:28.893 --> 05:30.939
for interviews, I think.

05:30.982 --> 05:38.033
♪

05:38.512 --> 05:41.036
- A guy that rants about
unreasonable searches

05:41.079 --> 05:44.300
doesn't sound like a good fit
for a government job.

05:44.344 --> 05:47.347
- Here's what local cops pulled
from Doug's car.

05:47.390 --> 05:49.610
- I think Doug wants
to take apart the government,

05:49.653 --> 05:51.133
not be a part of it.

05:51.176 --> 05:52.917
I finally found where he's been
lurking on the internet,

05:52.961 --> 05:54.179
on a site called Friction.

05:54.223 --> 05:55.398
- Sounds like porn.

05:55.442 --> 05:56.660
- Close.

05:56.704 --> 05:59.054
It's video games.
Gamers talking about games.

05:59.097 --> 06:00.795
I found Doug
in a discussion group

06:00.838 --> 06:02.231
about a defunct game,

06:02.274 --> 06:03.624
but basically,
it's just a cover-up

06:03.667 --> 06:05.234
for anti-government whining.

06:05.277 --> 06:06.801
- Whining or planning?

06:06.844 --> 06:08.759
- No plans, they just hate
on the government

06:08.803 --> 06:10.152
and talk about guns.

06:10.195 --> 06:11.545
It's all about protecting
your home

06:11.588 --> 06:13.329
when Big Brother comes
to take it from you.

06:13.373 --> 06:14.591
- Big Brother can have my crib,

06:14.635 --> 06:16.332
along with the rent
and the leaky toilet.

06:16.376 --> 06:18.552
- Puts a different spin
on what he was doing in Albany.

06:18.595 --> 06:20.205
Might have been scouting
targets.

06:20.249 --> 06:23.078
Government buildings,
government workers.

06:23.121 --> 06:24.122
- Nothing here.

06:24.166 --> 06:26.690
Just dirty laundry,
toiletries--

06:26.734 --> 06:28.562
- And a can
of men's body spray.

06:28.605 --> 06:30.128
What's the deal
with this stuff, anyway?

06:30.172 --> 06:32.435
You guys use it after a shower,
or instead of a shower?

06:32.479 --> 06:34.350
- That's getting
a little too personal.

06:40.356 --> 06:42.576
- Mass card from a funeral.

06:42.619 --> 06:45.448
Spencer Givens, Clifton, PA.

06:45.492 --> 06:47.319
The day Doug moved out
of his room.

06:50.801 --> 06:53.630
- The day he told his landlady
he was losing everything.

06:55.937 --> 06:57.547
- My husband Spencer
passed away

06:57.591 --> 06:59.941
almost two weeks ago.

06:59.984 --> 07:01.333
He knew Doug from high school.

07:01.377 --> 07:02.726
Pocono Pines?

07:02.770 --> 07:04.336
They survived
the shooting there.

07:04.380 --> 07:06.164
- A school shooting?

07:06.208 --> 07:08.906
- Yes.
They hid in a closet together.

07:08.950 --> 07:10.473
Spence kept Doug
from freaking out,

07:10.517 --> 07:12.127
and when Spence was wounded,

07:12.170 --> 07:14.434
Doug kept him from bleeding
to death.

07:14.477 --> 07:16.479
- So from that,
they became friends?

07:18.133 --> 07:20.178
- Mom?

07:20.222 --> 07:22.267
[baby babbling]

07:26.184 --> 07:27.664
There was a bond.

07:27.708 --> 07:30.580
Doug saved Spence's life,
and Spence never forgot that,

07:30.624 --> 07:34.105
but that's all they had
in common.

07:34.149 --> 07:36.151
Spence wasn't self-pitying.

07:36.194 --> 07:37.935
He didn't blame anyone.

07:37.979 --> 07:39.328
- Blame them for what?

07:39.371 --> 07:41.983
- He had chronic pain
from his injury.

07:42.026 --> 07:44.376
He took meds.

07:44.420 --> 07:45.508
He got addicted.

07:47.379 --> 07:50.600
He fought it real hard, but...

07:50.644 --> 07:52.776
we lost him to an overdose.

07:52.820 --> 07:55.605
[somber music]

07:55.649 --> 07:57.912
♪

07:57.955 --> 08:00.958
- We're very sorry.

08:01.002 --> 08:03.352
What was Doug so angry about?

08:05.354 --> 08:08.836
- He thinks the government
can stop school shootings,

08:08.879 --> 08:10.315
but won't.

08:10.359 --> 08:11.491
It's crazy.

08:11.534 --> 08:13.231
- Did you speak to him
at the funeral?

08:13.275 --> 08:16.800
- Yes.
I had to console him.

08:16.844 --> 08:20.282
He told me

08:20.325 --> 08:23.241
he'd make sure Spence
would be remembered.

08:25.417 --> 08:27.681
- Did he say how?

08:27.724 --> 08:29.552
- It was just talk.

08:29.596 --> 08:32.120
I don't need Spence to be
a symbol of anything.

08:32.163 --> 08:35.950
♪

08:35.993 --> 08:37.560
- That photo?

08:37.604 --> 08:38.822
When was that taken?

08:38.866 --> 08:41.259
- The one-year anniversary
of the shooting.

08:41.303 --> 08:43.044
Everyone posing
in their school colors

08:43.087 --> 08:44.741
to show the world they're okay.

08:44.785 --> 08:46.700
♪

08:46.743 --> 08:48.179
As if.

08:48.223 --> 08:52.401
♪

08:52.444 --> 08:53.881
- Pocono Pines High School,

08:53.924 --> 08:56.710
a 17-year-old student
with an AR-15.

08:56.753 --> 08:58.581
12 students
and two teachers dead,

08:58.625 --> 08:59.930
plus the shooter himself.

08:59.974 --> 09:01.845
20 people were wounded.

09:01.889 --> 09:04.195
- No doubt Doug was traumatized
by the shooting,

09:04.239 --> 09:08.156
and Spencer's death could've
sent him over the edge.

09:08.199 --> 09:10.245
He would've been on
an emotional hair-trigger.

09:10.288 --> 09:12.160
- First cops on the scene
at the school

09:12.203 --> 09:13.509
waited for reinforcements

09:13.553 --> 09:15.250
before they confronted
the shooter.

09:15.293 --> 09:16.730
- That was the strategy
back then.

09:16.773 --> 09:18.993
- Doug could harbor a grudge
against law enforcement

09:19.036 --> 09:20.734
for not intervening sooner.

09:20.777 --> 09:22.605
- He's hot off the funeral,
runs into a cop,

09:22.649 --> 09:24.738
and kaboom.

09:24.781 --> 09:26.609
- Hey, Kenny, bring up
that body-cam footage

09:26.653 --> 09:28.655
from the trunk.

09:28.698 --> 09:32.354
[tense music]

09:32.397 --> 09:33.485
Can you freeze that for me?

09:33.529 --> 09:36.271
♪

09:36.314 --> 09:38.621
Yeah, that's it.
Now blow it up just in here.

09:42.886 --> 09:43.974
A school jersey.

09:44.018 --> 09:45.193
I don't remember that

09:45.236 --> 09:46.542
being part of the inventory
for the car.

09:46.586 --> 09:47.978
- That's because
it wasn't there.

09:48.022 --> 09:50.633
- He must have taken it
with him when he took off.

09:50.677 --> 09:53.331
- Maybe it had
sentimental value.

09:53.375 --> 09:55.943
- Or he didn't want anybody
to see it.

09:55.986 --> 09:57.118
- Could be why he flipped

09:57.161 --> 09:58.946
when the cop
looked in the trunk.

09:58.989 --> 10:00.338
- Because he didn't want
to give away

10:00.382 --> 10:03.080
what he was planning next?

10:08.651 --> 10:10.131
- I haven't seen Doug Timmons
in two years.

10:10.174 --> 10:11.567
He used to come
to the memorials

10:11.611 --> 10:12.960
for the shootings.

10:13.003 --> 10:15.353
We do an assembly.

10:15.397 --> 10:18.792
- We're concerned he might be
a threat to your school.

10:18.835 --> 10:20.315
- I had the same thought.

10:20.358 --> 10:21.664
I activated
our safety measures.

10:21.708 --> 10:23.797
Extra guards,
active shooter drill.

10:23.840 --> 10:25.363
- That's good.

10:25.407 --> 10:26.887
- Please, sit down.

10:26.930 --> 10:28.366
- Thank you.

10:28.410 --> 10:31.065
Do you know why Doug stopped
coming to your memorials?

10:31.108 --> 10:33.371
- I told him he couldn't speak
at the assemblies anymore.

10:33.415 --> 10:34.808
The stuff he was saying
was offensive

10:34.851 --> 10:36.026
to the victims' families.

10:36.070 --> 10:37.854
[bell rings]

10:37.898 --> 10:39.421
- For example?

10:39.464 --> 10:40.596
- Doug believes the government

10:40.640 --> 10:41.989
allows school shootings
to happen

10:42.032 --> 10:44.034
to keep America's youth
in fear.

10:44.078 --> 10:46.558
- Did Doug find any supporters
for his views?

10:46.602 --> 10:48.169
- One, for sure.

10:48.212 --> 10:50.388
After we banned Doug, one of
the alums threatened to sue us

10:50.432 --> 10:53.696
for violating
Doug's free speech rights.

10:53.740 --> 10:55.567
- We'd like to talk to him.

10:55.611 --> 10:56.917
- Earl Hansen.

10:56.960 --> 10:58.483
Always trying
to get the school district

10:58.527 --> 11:00.050
to arm teachers.

11:00.094 --> 11:03.401
Thankfully, he moved out
of the district last year.

11:03.445 --> 11:05.490
I can pull his alumni file.

11:05.534 --> 11:08.232
- That'd be great.

11:10.887 --> 11:13.890
The memorials with Doug,
any videos on those?

11:18.155 --> 11:20.723
- This trouble with Doug--

11:20.767 --> 11:22.464
doesn't need
to change anything.

11:22.507 --> 11:25.336
Just have to move faster,
that's all.

11:25.380 --> 11:27.382
- I'm ready.
I'm not afraid.

11:27.425 --> 11:28.644
- Well, I'm afraid.

11:28.688 --> 11:30.341
Mike, what Doug did,

11:30.385 --> 11:32.735
and I'm not saying
he was wrong--

11:32.779 --> 11:35.216
but it puts a lot of eyes
on us.

11:35.259 --> 11:37.566
Let's just hit pause
until the heat dies down.

11:37.609 --> 11:39.481
What do you say, Mike?

11:39.524 --> 11:42.223
- There's no pause, Earl.

11:42.266 --> 11:44.007
You're in or you're out.

11:44.051 --> 11:45.095
- [sighs]

11:47.271 --> 11:48.969
I guess...

11:49.012 --> 11:50.144
I'm out, then.

11:53.190 --> 11:56.237
- Hey, Earl.

11:56.280 --> 11:58.065
Shoot him, Doug.
- Come on, stop kidding around.

11:58.108 --> 12:00.067
- Do it, Doug!
- You're nuts!

12:00.110 --> 12:02.634
[both grunting]

12:04.375 --> 12:05.681
- Come on, do it!

12:05.725 --> 12:07.074
Shoot him dead, now!

12:07.117 --> 12:08.597
Go ahead, Doug.
Shoot Earl.

12:08.640 --> 12:10.077
He's gonna jeopardize the plan.

12:10.120 --> 12:12.688
[gunshots]

12:12.732 --> 12:15.691
[intense music]

12:15.735 --> 12:19.913
♪

12:19.956 --> 12:22.567
- Hey.

12:22.611 --> 12:24.874
Shake it off, Doug.

12:24.918 --> 12:26.310
We're only getting started.

12:26.354 --> 12:30.967
♪

12:31.011 --> 12:32.577
- And they could
stop the shootings

12:32.621 --> 12:33.796
if they wanted to,

12:33.840 --> 12:35.537
but they don't.

12:35.580 --> 12:38.453
They could stop the ammo,
they could stop the guns,

12:38.496 --> 12:41.630
but they want us to be afraid.

12:41.673 --> 12:44.981
Our grandparents grew up
hiding under desks,

12:45.025 --> 12:46.809
afraid of nuclear bombs,

12:46.853 --> 12:49.116
and we grow up
hiding in classrooms

12:49.159 --> 12:51.292
afraid of gunfire,

12:51.335 --> 12:53.033
because the more afraid
we are,

12:53.076 --> 12:55.383
the easier it is for them
to control us.

12:55.426 --> 12:57.559
- He has a point.

12:57.602 --> 13:00.823
About children growing up
in fear.

13:00.867 --> 13:03.652
- You do that thing where you
hear about a school shooting,

13:03.695 --> 13:06.524
then you stay up all night
reading homeschool websites?

13:06.568 --> 13:08.788
- Angelyne and I used to talk
about it.

13:08.831 --> 13:10.267
- Anais is going
into preschool,

13:10.311 --> 13:12.835
but even that's
not safe anymore.

13:12.879 --> 13:14.750
- You know, they make
bulletproof backpacks

13:14.794 --> 13:16.752
and hoodies for kids.

13:16.796 --> 13:20.495
- Google that at 3 a.m.
after a school shooting?

13:20.538 --> 13:22.410
- I almost bought one.

13:22.453 --> 13:23.846
I didn't know
what kind of message

13:23.890 --> 13:25.587
I'd be sending Tali.

13:25.630 --> 13:28.982
I don't want her to grow up
scared.

13:30.026 --> 13:32.942
- Just located Earl Hansen.

13:32.986 --> 13:35.031
Not where you'd think.

13:35.075 --> 13:36.772
- I don't know
what's going on.

13:36.816 --> 13:38.469
The police just called.

13:38.513 --> 13:40.210
Earl was found dead
in the woods in New York

13:40.254 --> 13:41.951
outside Loudonville.

13:41.995 --> 13:44.736
He went hunting yesterday.

13:44.780 --> 13:46.695
- With who?

13:46.738 --> 13:48.610
- I'm not sure.

13:48.653 --> 13:50.133
Oh, God,

13:50.177 --> 13:52.309
our daughter's gonna be
coming home from school soon.

13:52.353 --> 13:54.746
- Is there anyone we can call
for you?

13:54.790 --> 13:56.487
Family, or--

13:56.531 --> 13:59.577
- My brother lives
in Allentown.

13:59.621 --> 14:01.188
- I'll help you.
- Thank you.

14:01.231 --> 14:02.406
- That him there?

14:02.450 --> 14:04.365
- Yeah.
- Kay.

14:04.408 --> 14:06.193
- Loudonville PD confirmed.

14:06.236 --> 14:11.546
Earl Hansen, shot twice
with armor-piercing bullets.

14:11.589 --> 14:13.504
- Just come as soon as you can,
Mark.

14:15.593 --> 14:17.900
[sobs]

14:17.944 --> 14:20.033
- Mrs. Hansen,
is there any chance

14:20.076 --> 14:23.036
your husband could've been
with Doug Timmons today?

14:23.079 --> 14:24.124
- Doug Timmons?

14:24.167 --> 14:25.473
What does he have to do
with this?

14:25.516 --> 14:26.604
- We're not sure.

14:26.648 --> 14:28.563
We thought Earl and Doug
were friends.

14:28.606 --> 14:29.956
- Well, they went hunting
together.

14:29.999 --> 14:31.653
The two of them
and this other man.

14:31.696 --> 14:35.396
Mike something.
I don't know his last name.

14:35.439 --> 14:36.876
He lives around Albany.

14:39.443 --> 14:41.228
- Is there anything else
you remember about Mike?

14:41.271 --> 14:44.535
Maybe something
your husband said?

14:44.579 --> 14:46.929
- Well, he has a foreign wife.

14:46.973 --> 14:48.583
She used to cook for them
when they went hunting.

14:48.626 --> 14:51.151
Earl would bring back
leftovers.

14:51.194 --> 14:55.111
Weird foreign stuff,
like meat jelly.

14:55.155 --> 14:56.939
- Kholodets.

14:56.983 --> 14:58.723
- Yeah, that sounds right.

14:58.767 --> 15:01.030
- It's a kind of Ukrainian
aspic.

15:01.074 --> 15:04.077
[phone rings]
- Oh, uh...

15:04.120 --> 15:07.297
It's my brother.
I have to take this.

15:09.343 --> 15:11.780
- So now you're an expert
on Ukrainian food?

15:11.823 --> 15:14.304
- I had a friend
from the Ukraine.

15:14.348 --> 15:16.263
- Another friend
you haven't told me about.

15:16.306 --> 15:18.482
- You didn't ask.

15:20.180 --> 15:23.096
- Mike from Albany
with a Ukrainian wife.

15:25.228 --> 15:26.969
Let's get Hana cooking.

15:27.013 --> 15:27.970
- We in business?

15:28.014 --> 15:29.537
- Here you go.

15:29.580 --> 15:31.800
- Kept it small.
Perfect.

15:31.843 --> 15:32.888
- Uh-huh.

15:35.021 --> 15:37.980
[dark music]

15:38.024 --> 15:42.506
♪

15:42.550 --> 15:43.986
- You have enough to eat?

15:47.685 --> 15:49.470
More American apple pie?

15:49.513 --> 15:50.471
- I'm full.

15:50.514 --> 15:53.474
Thanks, Lena.

15:53.517 --> 15:55.650
- You are so skinny.

16:00.133 --> 16:01.438
How is Earl?

16:03.832 --> 16:06.574
- Earl Hansen?

16:06.617 --> 16:08.489
Good.

16:08.532 --> 16:10.839
- Say hello to him for me
when you see him.

16:14.190 --> 16:16.584
[chuckles]
Isn't Doug skinny?

16:16.627 --> 16:18.281
He needs to eat more.

16:18.325 --> 16:19.761
- You feed him too good.

16:19.804 --> 16:21.545
He might never leave.

16:26.072 --> 16:27.464
Let's go to bed.

16:29.597 --> 16:30.902
Come on.

16:30.946 --> 16:37.997
♪

17:16.122 --> 17:19.081
- In all this time I was here,
it was not done correctly.

17:19.125 --> 17:22.215
It was too chunky,
so I want it chopped.

17:22.258 --> 17:24.695
Very, very fine chopped.

17:27.002 --> 17:28.351
[laughs softly]

17:28.395 --> 17:30.788
- You making kholodet?

17:30.832 --> 17:33.095
The gelatin and your accent.

17:33.139 --> 17:34.096
It's Ukrainian, right?

17:34.140 --> 17:36.577
- Yes.

17:36.620 --> 17:38.274
How do you know kholodet?

17:38.318 --> 17:39.754
- A buddy of mine
turned me on to it.

17:39.797 --> 17:42.104
- Oh.

17:42.148 --> 17:44.585
- Earl--Earl Hansen?

17:44.628 --> 17:46.152
You might know him.

17:50.243 --> 17:53.072
- That's quite a full basket
there, Ms. Kelerman.

17:53.115 --> 17:54.203
You have guests at home?

17:54.247 --> 17:57.206
[dramatic music]

17:57.250 --> 18:03.734
♪

18:03.778 --> 18:05.562
- FBI!
Freeze!

18:05.606 --> 18:06.607
- On the ground!
Now!

18:06.650 --> 18:07.782
- Hands, hands!
Raise your hands!

18:07.825 --> 18:09.044
- I'm not resisting,
I'm complying.

18:09.088 --> 18:10.263
- Face down, on the ground!

18:10.306 --> 18:11.699
- Face down!
- [grunts]

18:11.742 --> 18:14.441
♪

18:14.484 --> 18:15.659
- [grunts]

18:15.703 --> 18:21.187
♪

18:21.230 --> 18:23.319
- Clear!

18:23.363 --> 18:24.451
- All clear.

18:28.498 --> 18:31.849
This is Lima-1.
Suspect Timmons is MIA.

18:31.893 --> 18:32.894
- Jess?

18:32.937 --> 18:39.988
♪

18:47.038 --> 18:48.997
- Sierra-1.
Weapons are gone.

18:50.868 --> 18:54.176
- Dougie got away
with all the toys.

18:54.220 --> 18:55.656
- Each of these folders
has data

18:55.699 --> 18:57.788
on a state government
building in Albany.

18:57.832 --> 19:02.445
Number of agencies
in the building...

19:02.489 --> 19:06.057
number of employees,
emergency protocols.

19:06.101 --> 19:08.147
And here's a list
of nearby hotels.

19:08.190 --> 19:09.844
Points of entry, exit,

19:09.887 --> 19:12.325
number of floors, photos.

19:12.368 --> 19:15.632
These are target profiles.

19:15.676 --> 19:17.417
Government offices,
government employees--

19:17.460 --> 19:19.332
- And hotels
to shoot them from.

19:22.161 --> 19:24.511
He's planning a mass casualty
event.

19:24.554 --> 19:26.687
- And now he has the firepower
to do it.

19:34.085 --> 19:35.522
- No, I don't need a lawyer,

19:35.565 --> 19:37.437
'cause I don't recognize
your authority to question me.

19:37.480 --> 19:39.743
Your bureau is run
by the Deep State

19:39.787 --> 19:41.615
in violation
of the Constitution.

19:41.658 --> 19:44.835
- Actually, the FBI
is authorized under Title 28

19:44.879 --> 19:47.186
of the U.S. Code, Section 533,

19:47.229 --> 19:49.840
enacted by Congress
under authority granted

19:49.884 --> 19:53.192
by Article One, Section Eight
of the Constitution.

19:55.890 --> 19:57.674
- Now that we've cleared
that up,

19:57.718 --> 20:00.199
what do you have to say
about these files?

20:00.242 --> 20:03.506
- I am a sovereign citizen,

20:03.550 --> 20:05.160
subject only to common law

20:05.204 --> 20:07.031
as intended
by the Founding Fathers.

20:07.075 --> 20:09.295
Your government
is a false government,

20:09.338 --> 20:12.950
operating under admiralty law
to enslave its citizens.

20:14.300 --> 20:16.867
- I don't know about plans.

20:16.911 --> 20:19.479
I told you everything I know
already.

20:19.522 --> 20:22.699
About guns, about Doug in shed.

20:22.743 --> 20:24.266
- You are not taking this
seriously.

20:24.310 --> 20:27.269
- I--
- You helped a fugitive.

20:27.313 --> 20:29.880
A murderer who might kill
a lot more people.

20:29.924 --> 20:31.708
- I don't know Doug
is fugitive.

20:31.752 --> 20:33.971
He is just a man
Mike does hunting with.

20:34.015 --> 20:36.365
- Like Earl Hansen?

20:36.409 --> 20:38.715
- No, not like Earl.

20:38.759 --> 20:41.327
Earl is different.

20:41.370 --> 20:43.329
- What's Earl like?

20:43.372 --> 20:45.069
- Earl is happy guy.

20:45.113 --> 20:47.071
Is always happy.

20:47.115 --> 20:48.856
He make me laugh.

20:48.899 --> 20:50.858
And nice manners too.

20:50.901 --> 20:52.729
- You care for Earl?

20:52.773 --> 20:54.296
- I didn't say that.

20:54.340 --> 20:55.906
- You don't have to.

21:01.390 --> 21:02.739
- He's not like Doug,

21:02.783 --> 21:04.654
and he's certainly not like
your husband.

21:04.698 --> 21:06.482
He do that to you?

21:06.526 --> 21:08.310
[tense music]

21:08.354 --> 21:09.442
He's a brute, isn't he?

21:09.485 --> 21:15.535
♪

21:15.578 --> 21:18.886
You know who else
your husband hurt?

21:18.929 --> 21:22.237
- This isn't gonna be easy
for you.

21:22.281 --> 21:23.760
- [speaking Ukrainian]

21:23.804 --> 21:26.720
- Your husband and Doug
killed him.

21:29.505 --> 21:32.900
- Now we'd like your help
finding Doug.

21:32.943 --> 21:34.641
- They don't know
each other long.

21:34.684 --> 21:36.773
They meet three months ago
at Big Valley.

21:36.817 --> 21:37.948
- Big Valley, the casino?

21:37.992 --> 21:39.689
- Yes.

21:39.733 --> 21:41.865
And they hunt together,

21:41.909 --> 21:43.476
with Earl.

21:48.045 --> 21:51.005
- There's no evidence linking
Kelerman to Hansen's murder,

21:51.048 --> 21:54.182
but the A-USA can hold him
for harboring a fugitive.

21:54.225 --> 21:55.357
- Tell her to pile it on.

21:55.401 --> 21:57.881
We don't want Kelerman
bailing himself out.

21:57.925 --> 22:00.057
Same for the wife.

22:00.101 --> 22:01.842
- Doug was barely scraping by.

22:01.885 --> 22:03.974
He didn't have enough money
to gamble in a casino.

22:04.018 --> 22:06.194
- If he didn't meet Kelerman
at the blackjack table,

22:06.237 --> 22:08.631
maybe somebody at Big Valley
introduced them.

22:08.675 --> 22:15.682
♪

22:19.773 --> 22:21.165
- [sighs softly]

22:26.606 --> 22:28.608
- Molly Werner?

22:28.651 --> 22:30.653
I'm Agent Barnes.
This is Agent LaCroix.

22:30.697 --> 22:32.133
We'd like to talk to you.

22:32.176 --> 22:33.656
- Okay, sure.

22:33.700 --> 22:35.354
- You used to work
on the casino floor

22:35.397 --> 22:36.616
near the poker tables?

22:36.659 --> 22:38.444
- Yeah, but then I went back
to school

22:38.487 --> 22:39.619
so I couldn't work late nights.

22:39.662 --> 22:41.142
Why?

22:41.185 --> 22:43.492
- We're interested in
a customer named Mike Kelerman.

22:43.536 --> 22:44.537
Poker player.

22:44.580 --> 22:46.016
The waitresses over there
tell us

22:46.060 --> 22:47.888
that you're his favorite
waitress.

22:50.194 --> 22:51.631
- Okay.

22:51.674 --> 22:53.328
This is about Doug, isn't it?

22:53.372 --> 22:54.503
Doug Timmons?

22:54.547 --> 22:56.244
Can we...

23:02.729 --> 23:05.253
I was wondering when you guys
would find me.

23:05.296 --> 23:07.560
He's my half-brother.

23:07.603 --> 23:09.692
We have the same mom.

23:09.736 --> 23:12.434
- Thanks for not making us
play 20 Questions.

23:12.478 --> 23:14.741
- I know I should've
reached out to the police,

23:14.784 --> 23:17.396
but I don't keep in touch
with Doug anymore.

23:19.093 --> 23:20.442
I can't help you.

23:20.486 --> 23:22.531
- You know what he's accused
of doing?

23:22.575 --> 23:24.577
- Yes.

23:24.620 --> 23:26.970
I feel really bad
for those people.

23:27.014 --> 23:28.972
Doug was never violent.

23:29.016 --> 23:31.540
After Pocono Pines,
he was against guns.

23:31.584 --> 23:33.455
- When somebody's traumatized
like Doug,

23:33.499 --> 23:35.544
it can lead to paranoia.

23:35.588 --> 23:37.720
- We saw a video of a speech
he did at the school.

23:37.764 --> 23:39.113
- I know.

23:39.156 --> 23:40.767
He's always spouting
these anti-government talks

23:40.810 --> 23:42.464
to people who didn't ask
to hear them.

23:42.508 --> 23:43.683
- And some who did.

23:43.726 --> 23:45.075
Like Mike Kelerman.

23:45.119 --> 23:46.947
Did you introduce them?

23:46.990 --> 23:48.339
- No.

23:48.383 --> 23:51.734
No, they both came in a lot,
but they came in alone.

23:51.778 --> 23:53.214
- And when Mike
wasn't playing poker,

23:53.257 --> 23:55.216
he was hanging here
at the restaurant?

23:55.259 --> 23:58.132
- He came in here
for the slots.

23:58.175 --> 23:59.568
They give huge payouts.

23:59.612 --> 24:01.440
Better than the ones
in the casino.

24:03.746 --> 24:05.226
I have to get back to work.

24:05.269 --> 24:08.272
[tense music]

24:08.316 --> 24:10.579
♪

24:10.623 --> 24:12.668
- What if he reaches out
to you?

24:12.712 --> 24:16.150
- He really killed
those people...

24:16.193 --> 24:17.717
I can't help him anymore.

24:17.760 --> 24:19.327
- Call us

24:19.370 --> 24:21.808
if he tries to contact you.

24:21.851 --> 24:27.030
♪

24:27.074 --> 24:30.077
She's lying about Kelerman.

24:30.120 --> 24:32.253
The slot machines off the floor
pay out the lowest,

24:32.296 --> 24:33.820
not the highest.

24:33.863 --> 24:35.561
They don't want you
in the restaurant

24:35.604 --> 24:37.432
spending 35 bucks on a steak

24:37.476 --> 24:39.521
when you could be out
on the floor losing a grand

24:39.565 --> 24:40.740
at the blackjack table.

24:40.783 --> 24:42.219
- So she lied
'cause she did have a thing

24:42.263 --> 24:43.525
going on with Kelerman?

24:43.569 --> 24:46.136
- Or maybe they have
other interests in common.

24:50.967 --> 24:53.100
Crosby, I want surveillance
on Molly's phone

24:53.143 --> 24:55.189
and a full workout
on all her communications.

24:55.232 --> 24:56.451
We're looking for a direct link

24:56.495 --> 24:58.888
between her, Doug,
and Kelerman.

24:58.932 --> 25:00.107
- So we're thinking

25:00.150 --> 25:01.674
Kelerman got tired
of his wife's cooking?

25:01.717 --> 25:03.980
- No, I don't think so.
It was not about sex.

25:04.024 --> 25:06.156
Doug's politics
are about his trauma

25:06.200 --> 25:07.941
from the school shooting.

25:07.984 --> 25:09.290
Kelerman's the one

25:09.333 --> 25:11.292
spouting the mainline domestic
terrorist agenda.

25:11.335 --> 25:14.251
I think Kelerman
might've radicalized Doug.

25:14.295 --> 25:15.949
- The attacks
on government buildings,

25:15.992 --> 25:17.124
mass shootings.

25:17.167 --> 25:19.126
- Doug's reactive.

25:19.169 --> 25:20.344
He's unstable on his own,

25:20.388 --> 25:22.695
and he's influenced
by whoever's nearby.

25:22.738 --> 25:23.913
I think it would've been easy

25:23.957 --> 25:26.220
for Kelerman to activate him
to violence.

25:26.263 --> 25:27.787
- And somehow
Molly's part of it.

25:27.830 --> 25:30.006
- Well, she certainly knows
more than she says she does.

25:30.050 --> 25:31.660
- It's hard to tell
from her profile.

25:31.704 --> 25:33.619
She's a college student
majoring in history.

25:33.662 --> 25:35.142
She lives on campus.

25:35.185 --> 25:37.057
She has no criminal record,
not even a traffic ticket,

25:37.100 --> 25:39.320
but there's just one tiny gap.

25:39.363 --> 25:41.975
There's no record of her
attending high school.

25:42.018 --> 25:43.106
- That's pretty cool.

25:43.150 --> 25:44.543
If I knew high school
was optional,

25:44.586 --> 25:46.327
I would've enlisted
even earlier.

25:46.370 --> 25:47.850
- I mean, she was living
with Doug back then.

25:47.894 --> 25:50.592
He went to high school,
but she didn't.

25:50.636 --> 25:53.029
She just fell off the radar
after eighth grade.

25:53.073 --> 25:55.597
- Right after the shooting
at Pocono Pines.

26:00.080 --> 26:03.170
- Molly left our school in
the middle of the eighth grade.

26:03.213 --> 26:05.302
Her family decided
to homeschool her.

26:05.346 --> 26:06.782
I thought it was a mistake.

26:06.826 --> 26:08.697
- Whose idea was it?

26:08.741 --> 26:11.091
- Well, her mother said
that Molly was too afraid

26:11.134 --> 26:12.353
to come back to school

26:12.396 --> 26:14.442
after the shootings
over at Pocono Pines,

26:14.485 --> 26:17.097
but Doug was the one that
really frightened her into it.

26:17.140 --> 26:19.360
- He convinced her school
was too dangerous?

26:19.403 --> 26:21.928
- He convinced her that life
was too dangerous.

26:21.971 --> 26:23.494
He stifled her.

26:23.538 --> 26:24.974
After their mother
had a stroke,

26:25.018 --> 26:27.063
he had himself emancipated,

26:27.107 --> 26:29.196
and he took custody of Molly.

26:29.239 --> 26:30.197
She looked up to him.

26:30.240 --> 26:31.851
She believed every word
he said.

26:31.894 --> 26:33.940
- She believed
he was protecting her.

26:33.983 --> 26:36.333
He was her guardian angel.

26:36.377 --> 26:39.075
- You got it.

26:45.952 --> 26:47.431
- Molly.

26:47.475 --> 26:48.955
We need to talk.

26:48.998 --> 26:51.305
- I have a paper due tomorrow.
I told you what I know.

26:51.348 --> 26:52.436
- We don't believe you did,

26:52.480 --> 26:53.655
not about Doug,
not about Kelerman.

26:53.699 --> 26:55.265
- Kelerman is a perv, okay?

26:55.309 --> 26:57.093
And Doug, he's a baby,

26:57.137 --> 26:59.269
and I got tired
of looking after him.

26:59.313 --> 27:00.793
I don't care what happens
to him.

27:00.836 --> 27:02.621
- You care about
your guardian angel?

27:02.664 --> 27:04.013
Didn't you give him this?

27:07.800 --> 27:09.323
- It's just a cup.

27:09.366 --> 27:11.020
- A cup you made for your
big brother who protected you,

27:11.064 --> 27:12.239
who kept you safe,

27:12.282 --> 27:13.632
and now you think
you're protecting him.

27:16.983 --> 27:18.419
Molly, if you don't stop
lying to us,

27:18.462 --> 27:20.595
you're just gonna get him
killed.

27:20.639 --> 27:22.945
- You don't get it.

27:22.989 --> 27:26.122
I have to take care of him.

27:26.166 --> 27:28.647
He is so broken.

27:28.690 --> 27:30.649
So helpless.

27:30.692 --> 27:37.656
♪

27:44.271 --> 27:46.708
- I'm not trying to excuse
what Doug did.

27:46.752 --> 27:49.842
I'm just asking you to remember
that he's a crime victim too.

27:49.885 --> 27:51.017
- We know what he's been
through.

27:51.060 --> 27:52.322
- You don't know.

27:52.366 --> 27:53.715
He put his finger
in his friend's bullet hole

27:53.759 --> 27:54.847
to stop him from bleeding out.

27:54.890 --> 27:56.805
An experience like that
changes you.

27:56.849 --> 27:59.068
- It does.
It's called PTSS.

27:59.112 --> 28:02.115
He experienced a trauma,
and now he's hyper-vigilant.

28:02.158 --> 28:04.552
He sees danger
where there is none,

28:04.595 --> 28:06.119
and he reacts.

28:06.162 --> 28:08.164
Doug's extremely dangerous.

28:08.208 --> 28:10.384
We think he's protecting
a bigger plan

28:10.427 --> 28:11.907
he's cooked up with Kelerman

28:11.951 --> 28:14.344
and another friend,
Earl Hansen.

28:14.388 --> 28:18.261
A plan to kill
government workers in Albany.

28:18.305 --> 28:19.741
What do you think of that?

28:19.785 --> 28:21.003
Hmm?

28:21.047 --> 28:22.222
He's out there

28:22.265 --> 28:25.268
with guns and ammunition.

28:25.312 --> 28:28.402
We need your help
to bring him in.

28:28.445 --> 28:30.143
- You're gonna kill him.

28:30.186 --> 28:31.753
- Not if we can help it.

28:34.669 --> 28:36.889
Molly, I want you
to take a look around.

28:36.932 --> 28:39.892
I brought you here so you could
see what Doug is up against.

28:39.935 --> 28:41.763
- We have hundreds of agents,

28:41.807 --> 28:43.939
the state police of New York
and Pennsylvania.

28:43.983 --> 28:46.072
- High tech
Google doesn't even know about.

28:46.115 --> 28:47.682
- Your brother could call
from Mars,

28:47.726 --> 28:48.901
and we'd know about it.

28:48.944 --> 28:50.772
- And that guy right there?

28:50.816 --> 28:51.904
He can put a bullet

28:51.947 --> 28:53.253
in the middle
of a silver dollar

28:53.296 --> 28:54.645
from 100 yards.

28:57.474 --> 28:59.607
After the shooting,

28:59.650 --> 29:01.261
he kept you at home.

29:01.304 --> 29:02.697
Was he afraid for you?

29:05.831 --> 29:08.224
- He made me feel safe.

29:08.268 --> 29:10.618
And loved.

29:10.661 --> 29:11.837
- Okay.

29:11.880 --> 29:14.317
And you did the same for him.

29:14.361 --> 29:15.536
When he was hungry,

29:15.579 --> 29:16.972
you could've just given him
a doggy bag

29:17.016 --> 29:20.280
and sent him on his way,
but you let him hang around.

29:20.323 --> 29:22.282
He needed you.

29:22.325 --> 29:25.459
You're the only person who can
get through to him, Molly.

29:25.502 --> 29:28.810
You're the only person
who can bring him in safely.

29:28.854 --> 29:31.639
Now, will you help us?

29:31.682 --> 29:33.075
- What do you want me to do?

29:33.119 --> 29:35.034
- No more games.

29:35.077 --> 29:37.645
That's the first thing.

29:37.688 --> 29:41.605
- If he calls you,

29:41.649 --> 29:44.086
you try to talk him
into turning himself in.

29:48.699 --> 29:50.179
We'll be in touch
with some other ideas.

29:50.223 --> 29:52.355
One of the agents will see you
back to your car.

29:52.399 --> 29:55.358
[tense music]

29:55.402 --> 30:00.929
♪

30:00.973 --> 30:02.148
- I wouldn't give you
a donut hole

30:02.191 --> 30:04.411
for that girl's
cooperation.

30:04.454 --> 30:06.456
- She didn't exactly
convince me either.

30:06.500 --> 30:09.024
- Waste of a good dog
and pony show.

30:09.068 --> 30:10.939
- She's been lying to us
from the get-go.

30:10.983 --> 30:14.769
Texts to and from her phone,
after we raided Kelerman's.

30:14.813 --> 30:16.553
She gets a text,
"They got Mike."

30:16.597 --> 30:19.208
Then a second one,
"Can't do this on my own."

30:19.252 --> 30:21.907
She sends a text,
"I'll help you."

30:21.950 --> 30:25.040
- She's gone from enabler
to coconspirator.

30:25.084 --> 30:26.259
- To do what?

30:26.302 --> 30:28.130
Doug left behind his plans
for Albany

30:28.174 --> 30:30.785
and lost his coconspirators,
Kelerman and Hansen.

30:30.829 --> 30:32.569
- Maybe he's looking
for another target.

30:32.613 --> 30:34.441
- Molly can't say no
to her big brother.

30:34.484 --> 30:35.877
We can't change that,

30:35.921 --> 30:37.270
but maybe we can get them
to say yes

30:37.313 --> 30:38.837
to the right targets.

30:41.143 --> 30:44.886
Hana, show me what's coming up
at Big Valley Casino.

30:44.930 --> 30:46.801
- Everything is going wrong.

30:46.845 --> 30:49.673
When I get home, I get letter
from department of tax.

30:49.717 --> 30:50.849
- Revenue.

30:50.892 --> 30:52.154
It's called the Department
of Revenue.

30:52.198 --> 30:53.329
What did they want?

30:53.373 --> 30:55.070
- They say we owe tax.
We have to pay.

30:55.114 --> 30:56.855
- Call the phone number
on the bill

30:56.898 --> 30:59.422
and tell those bozos I'll get
it done when I get it done.

30:59.466 --> 31:00.771
I got bigger things
to worry about.

31:00.815 --> 31:02.121
- This is all because
of gambling.

31:02.164 --> 31:03.513
I tell you to stop,

31:03.557 --> 31:06.255
but always,
you have to be at that casino.

31:06.299 --> 31:07.561
- Again with the casino.

31:07.604 --> 31:08.823
If I wanted to be nagged
to death,

31:08.867 --> 31:10.303
I would've married
an American girl.

31:10.346 --> 31:12.174
- I am your wife.

31:12.218 --> 31:15.395
When you come home,
I want new plan.

31:15.438 --> 31:17.049
I want children.

31:17.092 --> 31:19.399
I want you to promise me.

31:19.442 --> 31:22.010
Hey.

31:22.054 --> 31:24.317
You say it.

31:24.360 --> 31:27.581
"I, Mike, promise Lena

31:27.624 --> 31:30.540
"that we will have new plan
to have children

31:30.584 --> 31:33.456
and live like real
American family."

31:33.500 --> 31:34.893
- Geez.

31:34.936 --> 31:38.244
- Say it, or I go home
to Odessa.

31:38.287 --> 31:41.421
- I, Mike, promise Lena
that we'll have a new plan

31:41.464 --> 31:44.467
to have kids and live
like a real American family.

31:46.948 --> 31:48.254
You happy now?

31:48.297 --> 31:50.038
- Yes.

31:50.082 --> 31:52.736
Very happy.

31:52.780 --> 31:54.608
- You get what you need?

31:54.651 --> 31:56.262
- Yeah, I got all
the right words.

31:56.305 --> 31:58.786
I just have to put them
in order now.

31:58.829 --> 32:00.962
- You did well, Lena.

32:01.006 --> 32:03.617
You have a promising career
as an actor.

32:03.660 --> 32:06.402
- I did this for Earl.

32:06.446 --> 32:13.453
♪

32:13.496 --> 32:16.543
[indistinct chatter]

32:25.682 --> 32:27.380
- It's Mike.
New plan.

32:27.423 --> 32:29.121
Casino.
The 8th.

32:29.164 --> 32:30.861
Department of Revenue.

32:30.905 --> 32:32.951
Tell him.
Get it done.

32:37.477 --> 32:38.695
- What's our girl up to?

32:38.739 --> 32:39.958
- Same, same.

32:40.001 --> 32:41.960
Serving food, clearing dishes.

32:42.003 --> 32:43.787
- The kitchen messed up
a dessert order.

32:43.831 --> 32:46.660
She spent her break eating pie
in the break room.

32:46.703 --> 32:48.879
- The Department of Revenue
event starts in an hour,

32:48.923 --> 32:50.098
and she's eating pie?

32:50.142 --> 32:51.360
- Crosby would.

32:51.404 --> 32:53.058
- We've had eyes on her
the last two days.

32:53.101 --> 32:55.669
She hasn't veered one bit
from her routine.

32:55.712 --> 32:57.236
- You sure she got
the Kelerman message?

32:57.279 --> 32:58.324
- Positive.

32:58.367 --> 33:01.544
She listened to it
and deleted it.

33:01.588 --> 33:03.329
- Maybe she didn't take
the bait.

33:03.372 --> 33:04.634
- It's possible.

33:04.678 --> 33:06.941
Her regular shift still ends
at, what, 7:00?

33:06.985 --> 33:08.029
- I'll check.

33:08.073 --> 33:10.597
Scheduling software
is an easy hack.

33:10.640 --> 33:12.338
Her normal shift ends at 7:00,

33:12.381 --> 33:14.557
but she booked a double tonight
till 2:00 a.m.

33:14.601 --> 33:15.863
- This is the college girl

33:15.906 --> 33:17.386
who didn't want to work
late nights.

33:17.430 --> 33:18.953
- When did she book
this extra shift?

33:18.997 --> 33:21.347
- She picked it up
three days ago.

33:21.390 --> 33:23.871
- Before we sent her
the Kelerman message.

33:28.267 --> 33:30.182
- The only government function

33:30.225 --> 33:32.401
at the casino
for the next two months.

33:32.445 --> 33:36.188
If we thought of it,
she thought of it.

33:36.231 --> 33:37.537
Call casino security.

33:37.580 --> 33:39.060
I want all the footage
for the last week cued up

33:39.104 --> 33:41.497
and ready to go
by the time we get there.

33:41.541 --> 33:43.064
She didn't take the bait

33:43.108 --> 33:44.848
because her and Doug already
had this plan in the works.

33:44.892 --> 33:46.241
They're ahead of us.

33:55.120 --> 33:56.512
- She's in no hurry.

33:56.556 --> 33:58.688
Getting dessert orders
and chatting up the kiddies.

33:58.732 --> 34:01.517
- I hope we're wrong.

34:01.561 --> 34:03.432
How are we doing
on last week's footage?

34:03.476 --> 34:05.086
- A week in the life
of a waitress.

34:05.130 --> 34:07.393
It's like watching
a documentary of a former me.

34:09.482 --> 34:11.092
- Okay, she's going
towards the bathrooms.

34:11.136 --> 34:12.398
- We have cameras
in the bathroom?

34:12.441 --> 34:14.922
- No, not the steakhouse
bathrooms.

34:14.965 --> 34:16.489
I'm gonna have to open up
the fountain area.

34:16.532 --> 34:17.620
- Not yet.

34:17.664 --> 34:19.448
- Got something.

34:19.492 --> 34:22.103
- Barnes, you keep a lookout
for her.

34:22.147 --> 34:24.584
- This is Saturday, 6:46 p.m.

34:24.627 --> 34:27.282
She took a room service tray.

34:27.326 --> 34:29.632
- Who's got the inside of
the kitchen service elevator?

34:29.676 --> 34:32.287
- Yo.
- We need Saturday, 6:46 p.m.

34:32.331 --> 34:33.723
Which floor?

34:36.161 --> 34:37.684
- Looks like 15.

34:37.727 --> 34:40.295
- Okay, we need video footage,
15th floor, last Saturday.

34:40.339 --> 34:41.514
- Don't have it.

34:41.557 --> 34:44.082
15 and 14 are closed off
from fire damages,

34:44.125 --> 34:45.300
pending renovations.

34:45.344 --> 34:46.867
The rooms haven't been occupied
for weeks,

34:46.910 --> 34:49.043
and the cameras haven't been on
for weeks either.

34:53.265 --> 34:54.875
- She's feeding him.

34:54.918 --> 34:56.529
That's where he has to be.
15th floor.

34:56.572 --> 34:58.139
She come back
from the bathroom yet?

34:58.183 --> 34:59.575
- I haven't seen her.

34:59.619 --> 35:01.882
Family of five are still
waiting for their desserts.

35:04.232 --> 35:07.105
- 7:48 p.m.
She's not coming back.

35:07.148 --> 35:09.498
All right, let's do it.
15th floor.

35:09.542 --> 35:12.066
Clinton, call in the SWAT team.

35:12.110 --> 35:13.937
I want the entire
fountain area clear.

35:13.981 --> 35:15.983
I want everybody inside.

35:16.026 --> 35:17.811
- Got it.

35:17.854 --> 35:20.814
[tense music]

35:20.857 --> 35:25.514
♪

35:25.558 --> 35:27.386
- I want you to go.
I'm serious.

35:27.429 --> 35:29.170
- I'm not leaving you.
You need me.

35:29.214 --> 35:31.303
- No, I don't.
See, I'm getting ready.

35:31.346 --> 35:32.739
I can do this on my own.

35:35.002 --> 35:38.092
- I am not walking away.

35:38.136 --> 35:40.747
Let me help you.

35:40.790 --> 35:42.705
- This wasn't even supposed
to be the plan.

35:42.749 --> 35:43.880
It was supposed to be
a building

35:43.924 --> 35:45.969
with a bunch
of federal offices.

35:46.013 --> 35:49.103
- Government is government,
Doug.

35:49.147 --> 35:51.540
This is still gonna send
your message.

35:51.584 --> 35:58.547
♪

35:58.591 --> 36:01.071
- For Spencer.

36:01.115 --> 36:02.290
- For all the kids.

36:02.334 --> 36:09.428
♪

36:26.271 --> 36:27.707
- Hey.

36:27.750 --> 36:29.230
Looks like people are going
away from the fountain.

36:29.274 --> 36:31.972
It looks like
they're moving them inside.

36:34.801 --> 36:36.585
What's going on?

36:36.629 --> 36:37.978
- I don't know.

36:40.633 --> 36:41.938
Here.

36:41.982 --> 36:45.246
This window overlooks
the parking lot.

36:45.290 --> 36:46.943
There's a bunch of people
down there.

36:46.987 --> 36:52.601
♪

36:52.645 --> 36:54.777
Just like we planned.

36:54.821 --> 36:59.434
♪

36:59.478 --> 37:00.609
[wood cracks]
- Drop your weapon!

37:00.653 --> 37:01.828
Drop your gun!
- Stop!

37:01.871 --> 37:03.482
Don't hurt him!

37:03.525 --> 37:05.788
- Doug, don't do it.
Talk to me.

37:05.832 --> 37:07.399
- It's what you want, right?

37:07.442 --> 37:09.531
All the government drones
can have their party

37:09.575 --> 37:11.054
and you save the day?

37:11.098 --> 37:12.795
- What about the message?
You die, the message dies too.

37:12.839 --> 37:14.667
- That's not true.
Don't listen to him.

37:14.710 --> 37:16.146
- It is true.

37:16.190 --> 37:18.540
The story will be "deranged man
suicides at casino."

37:18.584 --> 37:20.629
That'll be it.
End of story.

37:20.673 --> 37:21.717
- No.

37:21.761 --> 37:23.458
You're totally wrong
about that.

37:23.502 --> 37:26.722
They love talking
about school shootings.

37:26.766 --> 37:29.638
This is gonna put Spencer
and all the rest of the kids

37:29.682 --> 37:32.206
right back in the news!

37:34.730 --> 37:37.211
- Put your guns down.

37:37.255 --> 37:38.778
Everybody, put your guns down.

37:41.694 --> 37:43.304
All right, tell me
about Spencer.

37:43.348 --> 37:44.610
Give me the message.

37:46.916 --> 37:49.310
- The message is me
taking myself out!

37:49.354 --> 37:51.747
- Doug, give me the message!

37:51.791 --> 37:55.055
Hana, write this down.

37:55.098 --> 37:56.709
That way we'll get it right.

37:56.752 --> 37:59.755
- No, Doug, he's lying.

38:03.150 --> 38:04.804
- I wanna say something

38:04.847 --> 38:07.502
about thoughts and prayers,
for starters.

38:07.546 --> 38:09.504
- Thoughts and prayers?
What about them?

38:09.548 --> 38:13.334
- They don't work, okay?

38:13.378 --> 38:17.512
Thoughts and prayers
didn't help Spencer!

38:17.556 --> 38:20.472
- I'll tell them that.
What else?

38:20.515 --> 38:23.953
- All of the shootings
are part of a big plan, okay?

38:23.997 --> 38:25.651
And you have to tell
all the young people

38:25.694 --> 38:27.261
about the plan!

38:27.305 --> 38:29.132
- What's the plan?

38:29.176 --> 38:31.047
- The plan is to beat us down

38:31.091 --> 38:34.224
and turn us into slaves!

38:34.268 --> 38:35.791
If the kids knew the truth,

38:35.835 --> 38:38.533
they'd get off their knees
and they'd fight back!

38:38.577 --> 38:40.361
- You need to tell them that,
Doug, not me.

38:40.405 --> 38:41.493
- Please, Doug.

38:41.536 --> 38:42.842
You know what you have to do.

38:42.885 --> 38:46.019
- You have the passion.
You understand it!

38:46.062 --> 38:48.282
- I have nothing.

38:52.417 --> 38:55.463
- That's not
what Spencer thought.

38:55.507 --> 38:57.422
He believed in you.

38:59.249 --> 39:00.816
He wanted you alive.

39:04.298 --> 39:05.821
- I needed him

39:05.865 --> 39:08.824
to stay alive.

39:08.868 --> 39:10.260
- I know.

39:10.304 --> 39:12.262
He made you feel strong,
and now it hurts like hell.

39:15.657 --> 39:17.920
Doug, you've spent
your entire adult life

39:17.964 --> 39:20.227
trying to make sense
out of a senseless act.

39:23.970 --> 39:27.060
It's a burden the human heart
is not built to carry.

39:27.103 --> 39:30.803
Especially not the heart
of a 16-year-old kid.

39:34.328 --> 39:36.417
You have a choice, Doug.

39:36.461 --> 39:37.636
Give yourself a chance.

39:37.679 --> 39:40.290
Just put the gun down.

39:40.334 --> 39:47.297
♪

39:47.341 --> 39:48.647
- No.

39:48.690 --> 39:50.039
Just do it.

39:50.083 --> 39:51.606
Just do it!
- [cries out]

39:51.650 --> 39:55.871
- Truth bomb, Doug,
just like we talked about.

39:55.915 --> 39:59.353
If you die in that jersey,
you'll be a hero

39:59.397 --> 40:02.748
to all the kids out there
who grew up in fear!

40:04.010 --> 40:06.491
- Don't listen to her, Doug.
That's your own fear talking.

40:06.534 --> 40:08.057
- Fear?

40:08.101 --> 40:09.102
Doug, I love you.

40:09.145 --> 40:12.148
I want your life
to mean something.

40:12.192 --> 40:17.980
♪

40:18.024 --> 40:19.329
[gun clicks]
- [grunts]

40:19.373 --> 40:20.766
- No!
- No!

40:20.809 --> 40:23.725
- [grunting]

40:26.728 --> 40:29.383
[screaming]

40:31.559 --> 40:33.822
I'm sorry, Molly!

40:33.866 --> 40:36.956
- You blew it, Doug.

40:36.999 --> 40:38.348
You totally blew it.

40:38.392 --> 40:41.961
[both sobbing]

40:42.004 --> 40:49.055
♪

40:50.535 --> 40:51.666
- You all right, boss?

40:51.710 --> 40:53.668
- Might need a stitch or two.

40:53.712 --> 40:57.106
- Cool move, bro.

40:57.150 --> 40:59.195
- Secret Service guy
taught me that a few years ago.

40:59.239 --> 41:00.849
He didn't tell me
it was gonna hurt like hell.

41:00.893 --> 41:02.721
- We'll find someone
to kiss your booboo.

41:02.764 --> 41:05.811
- Thanks.

41:08.204 --> 41:10.163
[sighs]

41:10.206 --> 41:13.383
You see the look
on Doug's face?

41:13.427 --> 41:16.256
Is that what it's like to be
a kid in school these days?

41:19.999 --> 41:21.870
[exhales]

41:21.914 --> 41:28.964
♪

41:37.582 --> 41:39.322
- Just tell her to call me.

41:39.366 --> 41:40.933
- Okay.

41:40.976 --> 41:42.761
[children giggling]

41:42.804 --> 41:44.066
- Okay, I gotta go find my mom.

41:44.110 --> 41:45.067
- No, no, no.

41:45.111 --> 41:46.504
I'll go!

41:46.547 --> 41:48.506
- So you walking
the whole way?

41:48.549 --> 41:51.726
- Yeah, my mom said she would
meet me at the corner.

41:51.770 --> 41:53.554
- Yeah!

41:53.598 --> 41:54.947
[laughter]
- What's so funny?

41:54.990 --> 41:57.384
- Olivia, wait!

41:57.427 --> 42:00.430
[indistinct chatter]

42:00.474 --> 42:01.997
- Dad!

42:02.041 --> 42:03.346
- What took you so long,
sweetie?

42:03.390 --> 42:04.565
I thought you missed the bus.

42:04.609 --> 42:06.175
- Well, Gavin dropped
his water bottle

42:06.219 --> 42:08.090
and it spilled up and down
the aisle,

42:08.134 --> 42:09.744
and we had to clean it up
right away.

42:09.788 --> 42:11.267
Because you know what?
- What?

42:11.311 --> 42:13.574
- He had soda in it,
and that would stick.

42:13.618 --> 42:15.141
- It's sticky.

42:15.184 --> 42:17.143
- But you're not supposed
to drink soda on the bus,

42:17.186 --> 42:19.580
but Gavin breaks
a lot of rules.

42:19.624 --> 42:20.799
All the time.

42:20.842 --> 42:23.236
Come!

42:23.279 --> 42:25.934
So, do you wanna know
what we did on the field trip?

42:25.978 --> 42:27.588
- I wanna know everything.

42:27.632 --> 42:29.721
- Well, we learned about
all the Greek gods

42:29.764 --> 42:31.070
that the planets
are named after,

42:31.113 --> 42:33.812
and do you know that
since Jupiter is the biggest--

43:06.845 --> 43:08.586
[wolf howls]
